      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">37.201</ph> Definition.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <i outputclass="Term"
               xtrf="_37.201"
               xtrc="d2401e15"
               class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Covered personnel</i> means-<ol id="d2378e16" class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <ol id="d2378e20" class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e16">
                           <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> An officer or an individual who is appointed in the civil service by one of the following acting in an official capacity-</p>
                        <ol id="d2378e30" class="- topic/ol ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e22">
                                 <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> The President;</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e27">
                                 <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> A Member of Congress;</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e32">
                                 <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> A member of the uniformed services;</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e37">
                                 <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph> An individual who is an employee under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title5-section2105&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                       scope="external"
                                       format="html">5 U.S.C. 2105</xref>;</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e45">
                                 <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(v)</ph> The head of a Government-controlled corporation; or</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e50">
                                 <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(vi)</ph> An adjutant general appointed by the Secretary concerned under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title32-section709(c)&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                       scope="external"
                                       format="html">32 U.S.C. 709(c)</xref>.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ol>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e58">
                           <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> A member of the Armed Services of the United States.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p " id="d2400e63">
                           <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> A person assigned to a Federal agency who has been transferred to another position in the competitive service in another agency.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </p>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
